& [ResearchFindings] is the extracted mechanism boundary
  + [finding_001] is exponential decay is the best formal target for sealed-curvature intuition
    = meaning: resistance to unfolding can map to correlations dying over distance, but only after observables and measure/correlators are defined
  + [finding_002] is confinement and area laws are adjacent but not identical to the Millennium proof
    = meaning: Wilson-loop area-law or confinement evidence can support gap intuition while still needing continuum construction and spectral transfer
  + [finding_003] is lattice gauge theory provides rigorous partial footholds
    = meaning: finite or lattice results can show decay/area behavior in certain regimes, but the Clay problem requires the continuum four-dimensional theory
  + [finding_004] is a strong mass gap can imply confinement-type behavior in lattice formulations
    = meaning: directionality matters; confinement intuition does not automatically prove mass gap in the required continuum theory
  + [finding_005] is source sealed-curvature language has better fit to gap mechanism than to construction
    = meaning: it can guide what kind of decay/localization to look for, but not the existence of the quantum field theory

